body:
+1. LGTM.
@aaltay or @chamikaramj : please merge when you get a chance.
The generated python protos seems to have moved, which caused the rat check to fail. Updated the configuration.
The RAT issue will be resolved by #4027. We've had a broken config for some time and got lucky.
Ok. I did actually see your change and it still has old python path in it. I also wanted to exclude the Go protos.
The RAT check has succeeded, while including 2662 files. Since this is precommit breakage, merging.
Thanks. Any comments regarding the actual content in this PR?
The java build doesn't matter here, but just going to kick it.

R: @wcn3 for the Go parts.

Thanks @kennknowles. Sorry -- I should probably have asked for Go review first.
I believe the remaining failure in the Python precommit is that HEAD is broken. This can wait.
seems jenkins is not healthy recently. If this build still fails, let's hold for some time. Sorry for the inconvenience.
I’ve added a validation test to ParDoTest. It works with direct-runner. Is there a way to check if my test passes on the other runners?
Yes, you can invoke them by asking Jenkins nicely, like this...
Jenkins is not scheduling jobs. And anyhow I am going to slim this to just the commits to fix precommit.

TBR: @lukecwik. As you also noticed, these nullability issues were not addressed in the prior PR. My offline verification did not adequately represent our precommit. Unfortunately we also do not have Jenkins service right now, but should still move to fix the precommit for when it is restored.
@kennknowles tests are failing due to https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-3040, you can try re-running or running `tox` locally. It is unfortunate that we are blocking PRs on flaky tests.
Yes, the failed tests are OK. Beam tests are flaky recently, we generally need to improve them. In the context of this change they are fine.
Yes, I think based on personal judgment of the risk of a change we can move forward sometimes after careful manual validation.

Hi Eugene, thanks. And sorry, could not resist squeezing one more push into tikaio:-), it's to do with not failing the pipeline in case of the parse errors, as you suggested earlier. I thought it was a breaking kind of change so it would be rather done now, the configuration improvements can be incrementally applied later. Have a look please, hope that looks reasonable enough. FYI. I'm away from this eve till Mon eve so won't be able to react to the comments till next Tue. If my last commit only requires minor tweaks to make it right, then may be combine them with the other touch-ups you've had in mind. 
(Note, if Tika throws the parsing exception, the metadata may already contain some or all the file metadata, depending on the way a given parser operates, hence ParseResult still accepts Metadata with Throwable)
Thanks.
Closing this one, will open another PR.

Everything succeeded except for the coveralls report at the very end, see:
https://builds.apache.org/job/beam_PreCommit_Java_MavenInstall/15337/console
Thanks for the fix. This is included in #3969

Yeah, I actually also implemented failure handling similarly to what you did while merging the PR, but didn't finish it yesterday. It requires a bit more twiddling to get equality and hash code to work properly, because Throwable doesn't implement either of these things properly. I'm finishing this up right now and will merge soon.

@chamikaramj What do you mean by this
@nerdynick it is just a way to trigger Jenkins build. You can ignore it for now.
